{"type":"message","id":"3be5b214","parentId":"237796e6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:34:19.831Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4axbsxujk67i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 032837\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a single concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the key pending item is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression):\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most recent pulse log mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 032726.md`. There's also a reference to `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` which was just appended.\r\n\r\nA concrete action to advance this would be:\r\n1. Create the TIC experiment implementation script\r\n2. Analyze the pulse logs to extract invariants/variants\r\n3. Create a classifier\r\n\r\nGiven the \"stateless discontinuous agent\" nature and the emphasis on file edits, I should focus on creating or modifying a file that advances the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to create the TIC classifier implementation. Let me create a script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts patterns that are invariant vs variant\r\n3. Measures classification accuracy\r\n\r\nI should create a Python script or PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and create a concrete implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement, but the implementation hasn't been created yet. The pulse logs exist, but there's no classifier to extract invariants/variants and measure accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation script that will analyze pulse logs, extract invariant/variant patterns, and measure classification accuracy against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_content(filepath: Path) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract content from a pulse log, excluding metadata.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\r\n    # Skip header metadata, keep observation/action sections\r\n    lines = content.split(\"\\n\")\r\n    content_start = 0\r\n    for i, line in enumerate(lines):\r\n        if line.startswith(\"### OBSERVATION\") or line.startswith(\"## Pulse\"):\r\n            content_start = i\r\n            break\r\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines[content_start:])\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulses: List[str]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Extract patterns that persist across ALL pulses.\r\n    Returns: {pattern: frequency (should be 1.0 for true invariants)}\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    # Simple token-based invariance detection\r\n    all_tokens = []\r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        tokens = set(re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_]{4,}\\b', pulse.lower()))\r\n        all_tokens.append(tokens)\r\n    \r\n    if not all_tokens:\r\n        return {}\r\n    \r\n    # Find intersection = invariants\r\n    invariants = all_tokens[0]\r\n    for tokens in all_tokens[1:]:\r\n        invariants &= tokens\r\n    \r\n    return {term: 1.0 for term in invariants}\r\n\r\ndef extract_variants(pulses: List[str]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract patterns that change between pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    all_tokens = []\r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        tokens = set(re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_]{4,}\\b', pulse.lower()))\r\n        all_tokens.append(tokens)\r\n    \r\n    if not all_tokens:\r\n        return {}\r\n    \r\n    all_union = set()\r\n    for tokens in all_tokens:\r\n        all_union |= tokens\r\n    \r\n    invariants = all_tokens[0]\r\n    for tokens in all_tokens[1:]:\r\n        invariants &= tokens\r\n    \r\n    variants = all_union - invariants\r\n    return {term: 0.0 for term in variants}\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants: set, last_pulse: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content based on invariant structure.\"\"\"\r\n    # Simple prediction: next pulse should contain invariants\r\n    predicted_terms = list(invariants)[:10]  # Top 10 invariants\r\n    return f\"INVARIANTS: {', '.join(predicted_terms)}\"\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment(num_pulses: int = 20) -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Run the full TIC experiment.\"\"\"\r\n    # Get pulse logs sorted by date\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(\r\n        LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"),\r\n        key=lambda p: PULSE_PATTERN.match(p.name).group(1) if PULSE_PATTERN.match(p.name) else \"\"\r\n    )[-num_pulses:]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 3:\r\n        return {\"error\": f\"Need at least 3 pulses, found {len(pulse_files)}\"}\r\n    \r\n    # Extract content\r\n    pulses = [extract_pulse_content(f) for f in pulse_files]\r\n    \r\n    # Extract patterns\r\n    invariants = extract_invariants(pulses)\r\n    variants = extract_variants(pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate classification accuracy\r\n    total_patterns = len(invariants) + len(variants)\r\n    # True invariants classified as invariant: len(invariants)\r\n    # True variants classified as variant: len(variants)\r\n    classification_accuracy = 1.0 if total_patterns == 0 else (\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:29:03\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337659828}}
